Reuse of the "Information" under this licence

The "Grantor" grants the "Reuser" a non-exclusive and free right of free "Reuse" of the "Information" subject to this licence, for commercial or non-commercial purposes, worldwide and for an unlimited period, under the conditions expressed below.

The "Reuser" is free to reuse the "Information":
- to reproduce it, copy it,
- to adapt it, modify it, extract and transform from it, to create "Derivative information", products or services,
- to communicate it, distribute it, redistribute it, publish it and transmit it,
- to exploit it for commercial purposes, for example by combining it with other information, or by including it in his/her own product or application.

Subject to:
- mentioning the authorship of the "Information": its source (at least the name of the "Grantor") and the date of the last update of the reused "Information".

The "Reuser" may fulfil this condition by providing, through a hypertext link, to the source of the "Information" and ensuring an effective mention of its authorship.

This mention of authorship does not confer any official character on the "Reuse" of the "Information", and must not suggest any recognition or endorsement by the "Grantor", or by any other public entity, of the "Reuser" or of its "Reuse".

